    • codingEquals

      static boolean codingEquals(@Nullable Coding left, @Nullable Coding right)
      Tests for coding equality using only their systems, codes and versions. Two codings are equal if both their systems and codes are equal and either the versions are equal or at least one version is null.
      Parameters:
      left - the left coding.
      right - the right coding.
      Returns:
      if codings satisfy the equality criteria above.
